Channel Services (CService) - Database Migrations

Migration files for cservice schema updates.

Naming Convention
-----------------
NNN_description.sql

Examples:
  001_add_users_column.sql
  002_add_index_on_channels.sql
  003_drop_deprecated_table.sql


Example Migration File
----------------------
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS new_field VARCHAR(100);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_users_new_field ON users(new_field);


Checking Applied Migrations
----------------------------
To see which migrations have been applied to the cservice database:

  psql cservice -c "SELECT file FROM gnuworld_migrations WHERE module='cservice' ORDER BY applied_at;"


Automatic Migration Application
--------------------------------
Migrations are applied automatically when cservice starts. Simply:

  1. Place your migration file in this directory
  2. Restart gnuworld
  3. The migration will be automatically detected and applied

The migration system will log each migration as it's applied.
If a migration fails, gnuworld will exit with an error message.


For detailed documentation, see ../../doc/README.migrations
